717
00:38:02,847 --> 00:38:04,075
I think it's sentimental.

718
00:38:04,181 --> 00:38:05,546
Peggy.

719
00:38:05,650 --> 00:38:08,175
No, she's right.

720
00:38:08,286 --> 00:38:12,655
Just because it has sentiment
doesn't make it sentimental.

721
00:38:12,757 --> 00:38:14,418
We're talking about businessmen.

722
00:38:14,525 --> 00:38:17,961
Right. Businessmen
who like short skirts.

723
00:38:18,062 --> 00:38:19,359
Sex sells.

724
00:38:22,400 --> 00:38:23,799
Says who?

725
00:38:29,573 --> 00:38:30,631
Just so you know,

726
00:38:30,741 --> 00:38:35,974
the people who talk that way
think that monkeys can do this.

727
00:38:36,080 --> 00:38:39,072
And they take all this monkey crap
and just stick it in a briefcase,

728
00:38:39,183 --> 00:38:41,549
completely unaware that their success

729
00:38:41,652 --> 00:38:44,314
depends on something
more than their shoe shine.

730
00:38:53,364 --> 00:38:56,333
You are the product.

731
00:38:56,434 --> 00:38:59,597
You feeling something.

732
00:38:59,704 --> 00:39:01,331
That's what sells.

733
00:39:01,439 --> 00:39:03,737
Not them.

734
00:39:03,841 --> 00:39:05,968
Not sex.

735
00:39:09,980 --> 00:39:12,175
