810
00:45:59,990 --> 00:46:03,016
I will.

811
00:46:13,303 --> 00:46:14,827
Polly!

812
00:46:17,474 --> 00:46:18,566
I'm here, too.

813
00:46:18,675 --> 00:46:19,733
Hi, Daddy.

814
00:46:19,843 --> 00:46:21,071
Hi.

815
00:46:23,547 --> 00:46:24,844
Bobby conked out.

816
00:46:24,948 --> 00:46:26,279
Where were you?

817
00:46:26,383 --> 00:46:27,680
Mommy was late.

818
00:46:27,785 --> 00:46:32,188
I got stuck talking to Marilyn Keckner
in the parking lot.

819
00:46:32,289 --> 00:46:34,484
Well, I was here.

820
00:46:34,591 --> 00:46:35,888
Did you eat something?

821
00:46:35,993 --> 00:46:37,085
I did.

822
00:46:38,962 --> 00:46:41,396
Come on, show me
what you learned in ballet.

823
00:47:03,053 --> 00:47:04,577
Now I am quietly waiting

824
00:47:04,688 --> 00:47:06,553
for the catastrophe of my personality

825
00:47:06,657 --> 00:47:08,750
to seem beautiful again,

826
00:47:08,859 --> 00:47:11,623
and interesting and modern.

827
00:47:19,203 --> 00:47:20,898
The country is gray

828
00:47:21,004 --> 00:47:24,735
and brown and white and trees.

829
00:47:27,244 --> 00:47:31,305
Snows and skies of laughter
are always diminishing.

830
00:47:31,415 --> 00:47:33,940
Less funny, not just darker.

831
00:47:34,051 --> 00:47:36,042
Not just gray.

832
00:47:37,754 --> 00:47:40,985
It may be the coldest day of the year.

833
00:47:41,091 --> 00:47:43,855
What does he think of that?

834
00:47:43,961 --> 00:47:47,055
I mean, what do I?

835
00:47:48,432 --> 00:47:50,491
And if I do,

836
00:47:50,601 --> 00:47:54,537
perhaps I am myself again.

